Students of University of Abuja have decried increase in school fees and other levies in the university, which is forcing some of their colleagues to drop out of school. Some of the students, who lament the increase in school fees and other levies in an interview with LEADERSHIP yesterday, said that some of their colleagues are sponsoring themselves and would have no other option than to drop out if the situation continues. In separate interviews, the students also pleaded with the management to reverse the decision, saying that most of the students are sponsoring themselves and will not be able to continue with the hardship. A student in the Department of Economics simply identified as Mary told our correspondent that the management needs to assess the school fees and other charges in the institution. “Last session we paid N28,800 and this session we are paying N38,800, that is for social science and others like Geography are paying N48,000 or there about and the students are really complaining about it. “I’m calling on the management to do something about it, they can reduce the fees because it is really too much.” Another student, a Masters Degree student in the Department of Sociology who did not want his name in print said the new increment has affected every student in the university. According to him, “Collection fee now which has been N10,000 is now N30,000 and the acceptance fee increased from N4,500 to N30,000, so this is dangerous. “All these things are happening in a place where people are struggling to survive in an economy that is not favourable. As it stands now many students are dropping out because they cannot pay.” Meanwhile, the president, Students Union Government, Aluta Famous said the students representative has already made a request to school management to at least have 60-40 per cent of payment of the fees since a lot of students are finding it difficult to pay.